        {"type":"heading","value":"Simplest Explanation of Context API"},
        { "type": "text", "value": "The Context API in React is a way to share data or state across multiple components without having to pass it down manually through props at every level. It makes managing global data easier, such as user information, themes, or app settings." },
        { "type": "code", "value": "import React, { createContext } from 'react';\nconst MyContext = createContext(); // This creates the context." },
        { "type": "text", "value": "Provide the Data: Use the Provider to wrap the components that need access to the data. You put the data inside the box." },
        { "type": "code", "value": "const MyProvider = ({ children }) => {\nreturn (\n<MyContext.Provider value='Hello, World!'>\n{children}\n</MyContext.Provider>);};" }
         
